Madhuri Dixit’s secret winter face mask for dry and dehydrated skin🫂🤍

Ingredients:
🥛1tsp Milk (helps to gently hydrate and soothe the skin)
🍯1tbsp Honey (locks in moisture and promotes healing)
🍀1tbsp Aloevera Gel (hydrates, cools, and calms the skin, perfect for combating winter dryness)

🌨️Mix the milk, honey, and aloe vera gel together in a bowl to form a smooth paste.

☃️Apply the mixture evenly to your face. Leave it on for about 15 minutes to let the ingredients absorb into your skin. 

🫧Rinse off with lukewarm water for a soft, hydrated glow.

Lip brightening mask for dark, dehydrated and pigmented lips 👄 

Black to Pink lips naturally at home | Lip pigmentation removal lip scrub naturally pink lips

Ingredients:

☃️Vaseline - Locks in moisture and softens lips.
🍯Honey - Hydrates and nourishes lips.
🐝Turmeric - Lightens pigmentation and enhances natural pink tones.

🧺Mix 2 teaspoon of Vaseline, 1 teaspoon of honey, and a pinch of turmeric to form a smooth paste.

🌝Apply the mixture generously to your lips. Let it sit for 10-15 minutes.

🧣Use a clean cotton pad or a soft cloth to gently swipe off the mask.

Instantly softer, naturally pink lips with a brightened appearance💯🧁🎀

Say bye-bye to that pesky pimple‼️🤮

Ingredients:
🍃neem leaves 
🥐ginger 
🍯honey

1️⃣ Take a rubbing stone or mortar and pestle.
2️⃣ Rub fresh neem leaves 🍃 and ginger 🥐 together to form a smooth paste.
3️⃣ Add a few drops of honey 🍯 to the paste and mix well.
4️⃣ Apply the mixture directly to the pimples.
5️⃣ Leave it on for 2-3 hours, then rinse off with lukewarm water💦

Try it out and let me know your results💚

Comment ‘tan’ for recipe👒

दादी-नानी के घरेलू नुस्खे to remove tanning naturally🙈☀️

Ingredients:
🌻roasted turmeric 
🌝besan
🧁curd

🔥Dry roast the turmeric in a pan on low heat until you get a mild nutty aroma. Be careful not to burn it.

🥣In a bowl, take 2 tablespoons of besan. Add a pinch of roasted turmeric to it. Gradually mix in curd to form a thick, smooth paste.

👼Apply this paste evenly on your clean face and neck. Leave it on for 10–15 minutes to dry.

💦Once dry, gently scrub it off with lukewarm water in circular motions.
